ney.", "磨铁人:磨铁人是一个走街串巷的年轻人，专门为人们提供磨镜和磨刀刃的服务。他以其快乐的神情和积极的态度而闻名，总是带着愉悦的心情为顾客服务。无论是磨刀还是磨镜，磨铁人都以专业和热情赢得了人们的喜爱和信任。他的工作不仅帮助人们保持刀具和镜子的锋利与清晰，也为社区增添了一份温暖和活力。", "吊眼的汉子:The \"吊眼的汉子\" (Man with Slanted Eyes) is a character who serves as a companion to the knife sharpener, assisting him in his work. He is notably impressed by the quality of a long knife, specifically that of Tuoba Shanyue's blade. This admiration highlights his appreciation for fine craftsmanship and his role as a supportive figure in the knife-sharpening process. His slanted eyes are a distinctive physical feature that sets him apart, and his actions demonstrate his involvement and interest in the task at hand.", "长门修会:长门修会是一个由苦行修士组成的教派，其徒众以严格的禁欲生活方式著称。他们不信奉任何神明，也不主动传教，而是强调个人通过修行和探索来寻求真理。长门修会的修士们以知识渊博而闻名，他们乐于分享自己的学识，尤其对贫苦之人慷慨相助，因此深受尊敬，常被尊称为“夫子”。尽管他们自身生活简朴，依靠施舍为生，却常常将自己仅有的食物分给穷人，展现了极高的道德情操和无私精神。长门修会的修士们以其广阔的学识和慷慨的行为，在社会中赢得了广泛的尊重和敬仰。", "夫子:夫子 is a multifaceted character and title within the context of the provided descriptions. Primarily, 夫子 is a title bestowed upon a young knife sharpener, signifying his respected status as a member of the Long Gate Sect (长门修会). This title reflects his role as a knowledgeable and revered figure within the sect, as 夫子 is also described as a term of respect for the sect’s monks, who are known for their vast knowledge and their dedication to imparting wisdom to those in need. Additionally, 夫子 appears as a character in a text, where he is portrayed as a scholar or teacher engaged in discussing the intentions of a general, further emphasizing his intellectual and instructive role. In summary, 夫子 embodies both a respected title within the Long Gate Sect and a scholarly figure, highlighting his dual identity as a knowledgeable mentor and a revered member of his community.", "貔貅:The name inscribed on the knife, possibly indicating its origin or significance", "长刀:"], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-v3"}}}